natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all enzymes in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot annotated to catalyze reactions involving that lipid.
This query does not consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions and enzymes only for the specified lipid.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Example 16
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?uniprot
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?startId owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
  # federated query to UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .
    ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  }
} 
ORDER BY ?startId

# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/chebi/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uniprotEnzyme
WHERE {
  # Bind the URI for Ceramide (CHEBI:17761).
  # The user specified 'SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide'.
  # The entity linking identified CHEBI:17761 for Ceramide.
  # We assume the user's intent is to find enzymes for the lipid entity corresponding to Ceramide,
  # and CHEBI:17761 is the standard identifier used in reaction databases like Rhea.
  BIND(chebi:17761 AS ?ceramide)

  # Query the Rhea endpoint to find reactions involving Ceramide and the catalyzing enzyme.
  # Rhea reactions link chemical entities (via ChEBI URIs) to catalyzing enzymes (via UniProt URIs).
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/> {
      # Find reactions that are catalyzed (enzymatic reactions)
      ?reaction a rhea:Reaction ;         # Ensure the entity is a Rhea Reaction
                rhea:side ?side ;           # Reactions have reaction sides (substrates/products)
                rhea:catalyzedBy ?uniprotEnzyme . # Get the entity catalyzing the reaction (expected to be UniProt)

      # Check if the Ceramide entity is a participant in this reaction side
      ?side rhea:contains ?ceramide .
  }

  # Query the UniProt endpoint to verify that the catalyzing entity is a UniProt protein
  # and filter specifically for proteins in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot (reviewed entries).
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/> {
      ?uniprotEnzyme a up:Protein ;     # Ensure the entity found in Rhea is a Protein in UniProt
                     up:reviewed ?isReviewed . # Get the review status (true for Swiss-Prot, false for TrEMBL)
      FILTER(?isReviewed = true)     # Keep only proteins marked as reviewed (Swiss-Prot)
  }
}

natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all corresponding reactions (Rhea IDs and equation), as well as their enzymes as annotated in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot) enzymes themselves (ID and protein name).
This query does not consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions and enzymes only for the specified lipid.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Example 6
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?chebi ?rhea ?rheaEquation ?uniprot ?uniprotName
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?startId owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:equation ?rheaEquation .
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
  # federated query to UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .
    ?uniprot up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?uniprotName .
    ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  }
} 
ORDER BY ?startId
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?rheaId ?equation ?uniprotId ?proteinName
WHERE {
  # Query Rhea endpoint to find reactions involving Ceramide (CHEBI:17761)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find reactions that contain a chemical entity linked to the ChEBI ID for Ceramide
    # (The entity extraction identified CHEBI:17761 for 'Ceramide')
    ?reaction rhea:contains ?chemicalEntity .
    ?chemicalEntity rhea:chebi <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_17761> .

    # Get the reaction equation
    ?reaction rhea:reactionEquation ?equation .

    # Find the UniProt entry catalyzing this reaction
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?uniprotEntry .

    # Extract the Rhea ID from the reaction URI
    BIND(STRAFTER(STR(?reaction), STR(rhea:)) AS ?rheaId)
  }

  # Query UniProt endpoint to get details for the catalyzing enzyme
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Ensure the entry is a protein (UniProtKB)
    ?uniprotEntry a up:Protein .

    # Filter for reviewed entries (Swiss-Prot)
    ?uniprotEntry up:reviewed true .

    # Get the UniProt accession ID
    ?uniprotEntry up:accession ?uniprotId .

    # Get the recommended full protein name
    ?uniprotEntry up:recommendedName [ up:fullName ?proteinName ] .
  }
}
ORDER BY ?rheaId ?uniprotId

natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all corresponding reactions (Rhea IDs and equation).
This query does consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions involving the specified lipid and/or its more specific forms.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

# Example 5
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?id ?name ?chebi ?rhea ?rheaEquation 
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # Retrieve children lipids 
  ?id rdfs:subClassOf* ?startId .
  ?id rdfs:label ?name .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?id owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:equation ?rheaEquation .
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
} 
ORDER BY  ?startId ?id
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX swisslipids: <http://www.swisslipids.org/resource/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?reaction ?equation
WHERE {
    # Step 1: Find the corresponding ChEBI identifier for the given SwissLipids ID
    SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {
        BIND(swisslipids:SWISSLIPID:000399814 AS ?swisslipidsId)
        # Link from SwissLipids ID to external identifiers like ChEBI
        # Assuming rdfs:seeAlso is used to link to external resources like ChEBI
        ?swisslipidsId rdfs:seeAlso ?lipidCHEBI .
        # Ensure the linked resource is a ChEBI URI
        FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?lipidCHEBI), STR(chebi:)))
    }

    # Step 2: In Rhea, find all reactions involving the specified ChEBI lipid or its subclasses
    SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/> {
        # Find the ChEBI lipid concept itself and all its subclasses
        # obo:CHEBI_is_a* finds the concept itself (zero steps) and its direct/indirect subclasses (one or more steps)
        ?subClassCHEBI obo:CHEBI_is_a* ?lipidCHEBI .

        # Find reactions that contain any of these ChEBI concepts as participants
        # rhea:containsParticipant links a reaction side to a chemical concept
        # A reaction is linked to its sides via rhea:reactionSide
        # We need to find reactions (?reaction) that have a side (?reactionSide) which contains the participant (?subClassCHEBI)
        ?reaction rhea:reactionSide ?reactionSide .
        ?reactionSide rhea:containsParticipant ?subClassCHEBI .

        # Retrieve the reaction equation
        ?reaction rhea:equation ?equation .
    }
}

natural_language_question: Lipids affected by human enzymes
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/

PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX uniprot: <http://purl.uniprot.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX sl: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?lipid ?lipidName
WHERE {
  # Start by finding lipids in SwissLipids and their corresponding ChEBI identifiers.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {
    ?lipid sl:chebi ?chebi . # Link lipid URI to ChEBI identifier
    OPTIONAL { ?lipid rdfs:label ?lipidName } # Optional: Get the lipid name
  }

  # In Rhea, find reactions that involve the ChEBI identifier found in SwissLipids.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/> {
    ?reaction rhea:side ?side . # Get a reaction side
    ?side rhea:chebi ?chebi .   # Check if the ChEBI matches a reactant/product in Rhea

    # Find the enzyme that catalyzes this reaction.
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedEvent ?catalyzedEvent .
    ?catalyzedEvent rhea:enzyme ?rheaEnzyme .

    # Link the Rhea enzyme to its UniProt entry identifier.
    ?rheaEnzyme rhea:uniprot ?uniprot .
  }

  # In UniProt, check if the protein associated with the UniProt identifier is human.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/> {
     ?uniprot up:organism <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/9606> . # Filter UniProt entries by human taxonomy (9606)
  }
}
# LIMIT 100 # Optional: Limit the number of results for testing or performance

natural_language_question: What are the Homo sapiens genes associated with cancer and their orthologs expressed in the Rattus norvegicus brain?
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>

SELECT DISTINCT
    ?humanGeneLabel
    ?humanProtein
    ?humanProteinLabel
    ?ratGeneLabel
    ?ratProtein
    ?ratProteinLabel
    ?expressionLabel
WHERE {
  # Query the UniProt endpoint
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {

    # Find human proteins associated with a cancer disease
    ?humanProtein a up:Protein ;
                  up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Filter for Homo sapiens
                  up:disease ?disease ;
                  rdfs:label ?humanProteinLabel . # Get human protein accession

    # Ensure the disease is related to "cancer"
    ?disease skos:prefLabel ?diseaseLabel .
    FILTER (contains(lcase(?diseaseLabel), "cancer"))

    # Get the gene encoded by the human protein
    ?humanProtein up:encodedBy ?humanGene .
    ?humanGene rdfs:label ?humanGeneLabel . # Get human gene name

    # Find the ortholog protein in Rattus norvegicus
    ?humanProtein up:ortholog ?ratProtein .
    ?ratProtein a up:Protein ;
                up:organism taxon:10116 ; # Filter for Rattus norvegicus
                rdfs:label ?ratProteinLabel . # Get rat protein accession

    # Get the gene encoded by the rat protein
    ?ratProtein up:encodedBy ?ratGene .
    ?ratGene rdfs:label ?ratGeneLabel . # Get rat gene name

    # Find expression information for the rat protein
    ?ratProtein up:expressedIn ?expressionAnnotation .

    # Filter expression annotations for brain tissue (checking label/description)
    # UniProt expression annotations link to terms (like Uberon) and have descriptions.
    # Let's check the rdfs:label of the annotation or associated term.
    ?expressionAnnotation rdfs:label ?expressionLabel .
    FILTER (contains(lcase(?expressionLabel), "brain"))
  }
}

ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>


SELECT 
    DISTINCT
        ?uniprot
        ?uniprotID
        ?recname
        ?gene
        ?chebi
        ?uniprotName
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
     VALUES (?chebi) { (CHEBI:32395) }
     ?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
     ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
     ?chebi up:name ?uniprotName .
  }
  ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  ?uniprot up:mnemonic ?uniprotID .
  ?uniprot up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?recname .
  OPTIONAL {?uniprot up:encodedBy/skos:prefLabel ?gene .}
}

# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> # Often used for URI equivalence

SELECT DISTINCT ?uniprotID ?proteinName
WHERE {
  # Query Rhea to find reactions involving arachidonate (CHEBI:32395)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find reactions (?reaction) that have a participant (?participant)
    ?reaction rhea:hasParticipant ?participant .

    # The participant links to a chemical entity (?chemical)
    # Assume the chemical entity URI in Rhea is the ChEBI URI itself
    ?participant rhea:chemical chebi:32395 .

    # Find the enzyme(s) (?enzyme) that catalyze this reaction
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?enzyme .

    # Find the database cross-reference for the enzyme
    ?enzyme rhea:databaseCrossReference ?dbxref .

    # Filter for UniProtKB cross-references and get the accession ID
    ?dbxref rhea:db "UniProtKB" ;
            rhea:accession ?uniprotID .
  }

  # Use the UniProt accession ID found in Rhea to query the UniProt endpoint
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Construct the full UniProt protein URI from the protein accession ID
    BIND(IRI(CONCAT("http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/", ?uniprotID)) AS ?proteinURI)

    # Retrieve the preferred label (Recommended Name) for the protein
    ?proteinURI a up:Protein ; # Ensure it's a protein entry
                skos:prefLabel ?proteinName .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve human enzymes that metabolize sphingolipids and are annotated in ChEMBL

PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxonomy: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX sl: <http://swisslipids.org/rdf/>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?enzyme ?proteinName
WHERE {
  # Step 1: Find human proteins annotated in ChEMBL within the UniProt endpoint
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?enzyme a up:Protein ;
            up:organism taxonomy:9606 ; # Filter for human proteins
            rdfs:label ?proteinName ;      # Get the protein name
            rdfs:seeAlso ?chemblEntryUri . # Find cross-references
    # Check if the cross-reference is to ChEMBL
    ?chemblEntryUri up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/ChEMBL> .
  }

  # Step 2: Find reactions catalyzed by these enzymes in the Rhea endpoint
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
     ?reaction rhea:isEnzymaticallyCatalyzedBy ?enzyme . # Find reactions catalyzed by the protein
  }

  # Step 3: Check if the reaction involves a sphingolipid in the SwissLipids endpoint
  SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {
     ?lipid sl:involved_in ?reaction . # Find lipids involved in the reaction
     ?lipid sl:classified_by ?classification . # Get the classification of the lipid
     # Define the URI for the Sphingolipids class in SwissLipids
     BIND(<http://swisslipids.org/class/SL0101> AS ?sphingoClass)
     # Check if the lipid's classification is Sphingolipids or a subclass thereof
     ?classification skos:broader* ?sphingoClass .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Find mouse homologs in OMABrowser of human enzymes that catalyze reactions involving sterols (CHEBI:15889). Federating with Rhea and OMABrowser.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT
  DISTINCT
    ?chebi
    ?reaction
    ?humanProtein
    ?mouseProtein
    ?cluster 
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:15889
  }

  ?humanProtein up:organism taxon:9606 .
  ?humanProtein up:annotation ?a .
  ?a a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation .
  ?a up:catalyticActivity ?ca .
  ?ca up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .

  SERVICE  <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    ?cluster a orth:ParalogsCluster .
    ?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?node1 , ?node2 .
    ?node1 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein1 .
    ?node2 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein2 .
    ?orthoProtein1 lscr:xrefUniprot ?mouseProtein .
    ?orthoProtein2 lscr:xrefUniprot ?humanProtein .
    # inTaxon mouse
    ?orthoProtein1 orth:organism/<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162> taxon:10090 . 
  }
}

# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/Property/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX sio: <http://semanticscience.org/resource/> # Used in OMA for external references
PREFIX oma: <http://sparql.omabrowser.org/ontology#> # OMA Browser ontology (assumed)

SELECT DISTINCT ?mouseProteinAccession ?humanProteinAccession
WHERE {
    # --- Find reactions involving sterols (CHEBI:15889) and catalyzed by human enzymes ---
    SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
        # Find reactions where CHEBI:15889 (sterol) is involved
        ?reaction rh:involvedIn ?participant .
        ?participant rh:chebi chebi:15889 .

        # Find the UniProt accession of the enzyme catalyzing this reaction
        ?reaction rh:catalyzes ?catalysis .
        ?catalysis rh:uniprot ?humanProteinAccession . # Get the UniProt accession string
    }

    # --- Filter the proteins found in Rhea to be human proteins using UniProt ---
    SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
         # Match the protein by accession and filter by human taxonomy (9606)
         ?humanProtein up:accession ?humanProteinAccession ;
                       up:organism taxon:9606 .
    }

    # --- Find mouse homologs in OMA Browser for these human proteins ---
    # Note: The OMA Browser SPARQL endpoint URL is assumed as it wasn't provided
    SERVICE <http://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
         # Find the OMA protein corresponding to the human UniProt accession
         ?omaHumanProtein sio:hasPart ?humanExternalReference .
         ?humanExternalReference sio:hasValue ?humanProteinAccession . # Link using the UniProt accession

         # Find the OMA group this human protein belongs to
         ?omaHumanProtein oma:inGroup ?omaGroup .

         # Find another OMA protein in the same group that is from Mouse (taxonomy 10090)
         ?omaMouseProtein oma:inGroup ?omaGroup .

         # Check the taxonomy of the mouse OMA protein instance
         ?omaMouseProtein oma:part_of_organism ?omaOrganism .
         # OMA links organisms to NCBI Taxon IDs, often via sio:hasPart with the NCBI ID string
         ?omaOrganism sio:hasPart ?ncbiTaxonReference .
         ?ncbiTaxonReference sio:hasValue "10090" . # NCBI tax ID for Mouse

         # Get the UniProt accession for the mouse OMA protein found
         ?omaMouseProtein sio:hasPart ?mouseExternalReference .
         ?mouseExternalReference sio:hasValue ?mouseProteinAccession .

         # Exclude cases where the human and mouse protein are the same (e.g., self-homologs/within-species paralogs if group includes them)
         FILTER (?humanProteinAccession != ?mouseProteinAccession)
    }

    # (Optional) You could add another SERVICE UniProt block here if you needed
    # more details about the mouse protein beyond its accession.
    # SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    #      ?mouseProtein up:accession ?mouseProteinAccession ;
    #                    up:organism taxon:10090 .
    #      # Add more properties like rdfs:label for the mouse protein name if needed
    # }

}

natural_language_question: Proteins with binding sites for ligands similar to heme
predicted_query:
# Starting endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX uniprot: <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?protein ?proteinName ?bindingSiteFeature ?bindingSiteComment ?ligandChebiUri
WHERE {
  # Query the UniProt endpoint for proteins and their features
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Find resources that are proteins
    ?protein a up:Protein ;
             skos:prefLabel ?proteinName ; # Get the preferred name of the protein
             up:hasFeature ?bindingSiteFeature . # Link the protein to its features

    # Filter features to find binding sites
    ?bindingSiteFeature a up:Binding_Site ;
                        rdfs:comment ?bindingSiteComment . # Get the comment for the binding site (often describes the ligand)

    # Optional: Try to find a cross-reference from the binding site feature to ChEBI for the ligand
    OPTIONAL {
      ?bindingSiteFeature up:crossReference ?chebiRef .
      ?chebiRef a up:Chem_Ref ; # Ensure the cross-reference is a chemical reference
                up:db <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/ChEBI> ; # Ensure the database is ChEBI
                up:id ?chebiIdLiteral . # Get the ChEBI ID as a literal (e.g., "CHEBI:16488")

      # Convert the ChEBI ID literal to an integer and construct the ChEBI URI
      BIND(xsd:integer(REPLACE(STR(?chebiIdLiteral), "CHEBI:", "")) AS ?chebiIdInt)
      BIND(chebi:?chebiIdInt AS ?ligandChebiUri)
    }

    # Filter for binding sites where the ligand is Heme or similar.
    # This is approximated by checking specific ChEBI IDs for Heme (CHEBI:16488, CHEBI:147291)
    # or by searching for the term "heme" within the binding site comment.
    FILTER (
       # Check if the found ChEBI URI is for generic Heme or a specific Heme variant
       (?ligandChebiUri = chebi:16488 || ?ligandChebiUri = chebi:147291) ||
       # Alternatively, check if the comment text contains "heme" (case-insensitive)
       CONTAINS(LCASE(?bindingSiteComment), "heme")
    )
  }
}

predicted_query:
# Endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?metabolite ?metaboliteLabel
WHERE {
  # Start by finding all UniProt entries for Homo sapiens (Human).
  # We use the SPARQL endpoint for UniProt.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprotEntry up:organism taxon:9606 .
  }

  # Now, using the human UniProt entries, find the biochemical reactions
  # from Rhea-DB that are catalyzed by these human proteins.
  # Query the Rhea-DB SPARQL endpoint.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find Rhea catalytic activities linked to the human UniProt entries
    ?catalyticActivity rhea:uniprotEntry ?uniprotEntry .

    # Find the specific Rhea reactions associated with these catalytic activities
    ?reaction rhea:catalyticActivity ?catalyticActivity .

    # Identify the participants (substrates and products) in these reactions.
    # These participants are the metabolites involved in human biochemical reactions.
    ?reaction rhea:participant ?metabolite .

    # Filter to ensure the participant URIs are from the ChEBI ontology,
    # as Rhea typically uses ChEBI for chemical entities (metabolites).
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?metabolite), STR(chebi:)))

    # Attempt to retrieve the human-readable label for the metabolite from Rhea.
    # Using OPTIONAL so that metabolites without labels are still included.
    OPTIONAL { ?metabolite rdfs:label ?metaboliteLabel . }
  }
}

  # Query the Rhea endpoint to find reactions catalyzed by enzymes
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find reactions ?reaction that are catalyzed by an enzyme protein ?enzymeUniProtURI
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?enzymeUniProtURI .
    # Ensure it's a reaction (optional, could add more specific types if needed)
    # ?reaction a rhea:Reaction ; # rhea:catalyzedBy already implies a reaction
  }

  # Query the UniProt endpoint to get the EC number for the enzyme protein
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Use the UniProt URI obtained from Rhea
    ?enzymeUniProtURI a uniprot:Protein ;
                      uniprot:ec ?ecNumberLiteral . # Get the EC number literal (e.g., "1.1.1.1")
  }

  # Extract the first part of the EC number string
  # EC numbers are typically in the format X.Y.Z.W
  # We want X, which is the substring before the first dot "."
  BIND(STRBEFORE(STR(?ecNumberLiteral), ".") AS ?firstEcClass)

  # Filter out cases where the EC number literal might not contain a dot
  # (although standard EC numbers always do)
  FILTER(?firstEcClass != "")

}
# Group the results by the extracted first EC class
GROUP BY ?firstEcClass
# Order the results by the count of reactions in descending order
ORDER BY DESC(?reactionCount)

ground_truth_query:
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX rdfs:<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX skos:<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>

SELECT
  ?ecClass
  (str(?ecName) as ?ecClassName)
  (count(?reaction) as ?reactionCount)
WHERE
{
  SERVICE <http://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    VALUES (?ecClass) { (ec:1.-.-.-)(ec:2.-.-.-)(ec:3.-.-.-)(ec:4.-.-.-)(ec:5.-.-.-) (ec:6.-.-.-) (ec:7.-.-.-) }
    ?ecNumber rdfs:subClassOf ?ecClass .
    ?ecClass skos:prefLabel ?ecName .
  }
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
}
GROUP BY ?ecClass ?ecName

# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT ?firstLevel (COUNT(DISTINCT ?reaction) AS ?reactionCount)
WHERE {
  # Find reactions in Rhea that are catalyzed by a UniProt entry (enzyme)
  ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?uniprotEntry .

  # Query UniProt to get the EC number(s) associated with the enzyme
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Use up:ecName to get the string representation of the EC number (e.g., "1.1.1.1")
    ?uniprotEntry up:ecName ?ecLiteral .

    # Extract the first level (the digit before the first dot) from the EC number string
    BIND(STRBEFORE(?ecLiteral, ".") AS ?firstLevel)

    # Filter to include only valid first-level EC numbers (1 through 7)
    FILTER(REGEX(?firstLevel, "^[1-7]$"))
  }
  # Note: A reaction might be catalyzed by multiple enzymes with different EC numbers,
  # or an enzyme might have multiple EC numbers. This query counts a reaction
  # towards each unique first-level EC associated with any catalyzing enzyme.
}
GROUP BY ?firstLevel
ORDER BY ?firstLevel

natural_language_question: Select all Rhea reactions linked to protein sequences (enzymes and transporters) in UniProtKB
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Query 12
# Select all Rhea reactions used to annotate enzyme sequences in UniProtKB
# return the number of UniProtKB entries
# Federated query using a service to UniProt SPARQL endpoint
#
# This query corresponds to the Rhea website query:
# https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=uniprot:*
#
SELECT ?uniprotCount ?rhea ?accession ?equation 
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> { 
  	SELECT ?rhea (count(?uniprot) as ?uniprotCount) {
      ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea . 
  	}
  	GROUP BY ?rhea
  }
  ?rhea rh:accession ?accession .
  ?rhea rh:equation ?equation .
}

PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?reaction
WHERE {
  # Query UniProt to find protein entries that link to Rhea resources
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Find any resource ?rheaResource linked from a UniProt protein ?protein
    ?protein rdfs:seeAlso ?rheaResource .

    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?rheaResource), "http://rdf.rhea-db.org/"))

  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Check if the resource URI obtained from UniProt is of type rhea:Reaction
    ?rheaResource a rhea:Reaction .

    # Use the verified Rhea Reaction URI as the result
    BIND(?rheaResource AS ?reaction)
  }
}

natural_language_question: Search for Chemical names starting in Japanese, translated to english using allie
Retrieve parent reactions (and their catalyzing enzymes) for a metabolite that is not directly involved in a reaction (ex: CHEBI:83137).
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX up:<http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX keywords:<http://purl.uniprot.org/keywords/>

SELECT
  ?chebi
  ?ecNumber
  (count(?protein) as ?proteinCount)
  ?reaction
  ?equation
WHERE {
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:equation ?equation .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  CHEBI:83137 rdfs:subClassOf+ ?chebi.

  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
  ?protein a up:Protein .
  ?protein up:reviewed true .
    {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber} .
  }
} 
GROUP BY ?chebi ?ecNumber ?reaction ?equation

natural_language_question: Retrieve the set of metabolites involved in reactions catalyzed by human genes (HUMAN reference proteome)
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX rdfs:<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX up:<http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX keywords:<http://purl.uniprot.org/keywords/>

SELECT
  ?chebi
  ?reaction
  ?ecNumber
  ?protein
  ?ensemblTranscript
  ?ensemblGene
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a up:Protein .
    ?protein up:reviewed true .
    ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 .
    ?protein up:classifiedWith keywords:1185 .

    ?protein rdfs:seeAlso ?ensemblTranscript .
    ?ensemblTranscript a up:Transcript_Resource .
    ?ensemblTranscript up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/Ensembl> .
    ?ensemblTranscript up:transcribedFrom ?ensemblGene .

      {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber .}
    UNION
      {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber .}
    UNION
      {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber .}
  }

  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi . # only considering small molecules participants
}
